Best burger in Brooklyn!! Also the meatloaf sandwich is incredibly delicious either  with tots or fries! But the entire menu is great and highly recommend.

I like this little place. The burgers are fantastic and a really good value. It's not one of those pretentious burger joints that charges you, like, $28 for some bizarre meat blend with a vague artisanal cheese. You get a nice burger, cooked to perfection, on a Martin's potato roll. Nice nice.  My girlfriend doesn't even like Martin's rolls and still likes the place because the burger is that good.  I've also had the fried tilapia sandwich, which was legit.  And don't forget to have the tots with the spicy mayo concoction.
Easily some of the best sweet potato fries in Brooklyn.

Mothers is has the feel of a neighborhood bar with great food options. Somewhere you bring friends and lovers alike, run into people you know. Have a few pints and burger why don't ya, and don't forget the tots!
A neighborhood favorite

We arrived at this place for dinner. we heard about this place from many people.  Well, it was a winning. The staff were extremely nice and we felt excellent. The meal was great. We loved this restaurant very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Recommended.
Very good burgers for the price and decent beer selection.
Mother's is always good. A bit crowded at times but worth the wait. Good food and drink list, good service, reasonably priced. Great back yard too!

The food was good, with the bacon nicely cooked. Feels like a place that doesn't try to overdo it, and the prices were quite reasonable.

Hands down the BEST turkey burger and sweet potato fries I've ever had! Typically sweet potatoes fries are always overly sweet tasting, but these are thinly sliced and have thick chunks of salt on them, so the sweetness is cut down by a good amount. Also paired it with a Snakebite (cider + lager). A perfectly delicious tasting meal overall!!  Edit: Got the banana cream pudding for dessert... Amazing!!! Definitely get that as well. Great portion size too.

These burgers are banging!!! High quality beef, thick patty with juices flowing into the bun. Sitting on top of a mound of fries - I got sweet potato but they have regular or tots too. Pickle, onions, tomato and lettuce are crispy and fresh. Came with a spicy zesty sauce off some kind. Everything delicious, texture, temperature, yum...  Service was friendly and prompt, bartender/ server was cool dude. The lunch special included a half pint of beer too, all for 12 bucks! You need to try this place, if you haven't already. They've been here for many years so likely that you have been here already, but if not then come through!

Let's get this out of the way:  the food is great, and I like their beer selection.  However, twice in a row now I've ordered a veggie burger and got a meat burger instead.  I'm not _that_ strict about it, and I'd rather eat it than have it be thrown away, but twice in a row is pretty ridiculous.  I've crossed it off my list of places I'll eat regularly because of this.  If you don't care about that, it's four stars.

The burgers used to be really good here but I do not know what happened. Things have definitely changed. Firstly, my burger was charred beyond recognition and honestly, I do not think eating a burnt burger is all that healthy for you. Secondly, the bun is different. It used to be a sesame seed bun and this one is just a regular plain potato bun (not even toasted). Lastly, the tangy mayo sauce used to quite delicious, but now they have added a spicy kick to it and for someone who can not take too much spice, they should give people an alternative like a non-spicy version that is not ketchup. The quality does not justify the price. Sadly, if burger king can make it taste better for cheaper, then I would say skip it.

Apparently you must be white to be served here. Between 8:00-8:15 on Friday, 12/11, I sat at the bar to enjoy their highly remarked burger, but to no avail. I waved my hands to get both bartenders attention as they served 6 people instead of me. Yes, I began counting as I sat for 15 mins. Mind you, the count were of those walking in after me - one couple with a friend, one single male, and two males. The couple with the friend sat at the table across from the bar, the single male sat approximately three seats away, and the two males at the other end. I was the only person of color in the entire establishment, or at least of a darker skin tone. Appalling.
